// And 'go' is not implemented on T, 'self.go()' resolves to Foo::go(),
// causing a stack overflow at runtime.
//
// THE SOLUTION: Isolate the method call in a private module where
// the Trait is NOT in scope. This forces resolution to T's inherent method.
// If T::go doesn't exist, this fails at COMPILE TIME, not runtime.

